{"id":"cl-t07","title":"Brainstorm: Help users write better prompt.md files","description":"The actor-critic system correctly evaluates what's in the prompt, but users may write incomplete prompts (missing documentation requirements, test requirements, etc.). Explore ways to help users write more complete prompts:\n\nOptions to explore:\n1. Prompt templates with checklists (docs, tests, verification steps)\n2. A 'codeloops lint' command that scans prompt.md for common omissions\n3. Structured prompt format (YAML/TOML) with explicit requirements section\n4. Pre-flight check that asks user 'Did you include X, Y, Z?'\n5. Integration with the brainstorming skill to help refine prompts before execution\n\nContext: A recent session completed successfully but missed documentation updates because they weren't included in prompt.md despite being discussed in the planning conversation.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-01-26T07:48:50.593294978-05:00","updated_at":"2026-01-26T07:48:58.78861754-05:00"}
